Kerry Attacks Trump's Wall Proposal, Tells Northeastern Univ Grads to Prepare for 'Borderless World'

On Friday, Secretary of State John Kerry took a shot at likely presumptive GOP presidential nominee Donald Trump, particularly for his proposed border wall, during his commencement address at Northeastern University in Boston.

RYAN'S CHALLENGER: Ryan has 'some nerve' not supporting Trump

On today's program, Rep. Paul Ryan's (R-WI) primary opponent, Paul Nehlen, discussed his campaign to unseat the Speaker of the House. Nehlen, who currently serves as Senior Vice President of Operations for Neptune Benson, explained, "the reason I'm running for Congress is, Paul Ryan is the mercenary champion of this Trans Pacific Partnership, this job killing, industry destroying trade deal." Nehlen explained, "in business, you succeed by under promising and over-delivering...But, in politics, you can fail year after year and yet, the corruption of Washington D.C. gets protected by big donor money." He hopes, by unseating the current speaker, to end that cycle of corruption
